Name: /if:interfaces/if:interface/if:name
Description: A short name uniquely describing an interface, eg "Eth1/0".
References: See [RFC2863] for the definition of the ifName object.

Name: /if:interfaces/if:interface/if:description
Description:
The description of an interface, eg "FastEthernet 1/0" or "ISP 
connection".
References: See [RFC2863] for the definition of the ifDescr object.

Name: /if:interfaces/if:interface/if:type
Description: The type of an interface, eg ""

Name: /if:interfaces/if:interface/if:enabled
Description: This leaf contains the configured, desired state of the  interface.

Name: /if:interfaces-state/if:interface/if:admin-status
Description: The desired state of the interface.    This leaf has the same read semantics as ifAdminStatus.
